  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The main aim is to demonstrate whether the high flow conditioned oxygen therapy reduces the
      reintubation rate. Post-extubation respiratory failure risk will be stratified (as the
      randomization). In high risk patients high flow conditioned oxygen therapy will be compared
      with with not conditioned non-invasive mechanical ventilation. In low risk patients
      comparison will be conventional oxygen therapy. Hypercapnic patients will be excluded.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
